      • getDefaultSelectedTerm

        protected Term getDefaultSelectedTerm()
        Description copied from class: Query
        The default selected term when select* methods are called without specifying a select term By default, a PrologEngineQuery uses its goal. QueryAdapter queries use their adapted default selected term. Other QueryAdapter classes may find useful to override this method. For example, ExceptionHandledQuery overrides this method so it is the first argument in the catch block of the original goal. Logtalk queries overrides this so the default selected term is the Logtalk method and parameters (excluding the id of the Logtalk object and the :: operator)
